OL,3,CHousehold energy bills rise as
OL,4,Ctemperatures plummet
OL,6,FMany households' energy bills will
OL,7,Frise from today, just as a swathe of
OL,8,Fcold health alerts have been issued
OL,9,Ffor large areas of the UK.
OL,11,FThe 0.2% increase to Ofgem's energy
OL,12,Fprice cap will equate to a rise of
OL,13,Fabout 28p a month for the average
OL,14,Fhousehold in England, Wales and
OL,15,FScotland remaining on a standard
OL,16,Fvariable tariff.
OL,18,FThis amounts to an average overall
OL,19,Fbill of #1,758 a year, up from the
OL,20,Fcurrent #1,755.
