OL,3,CHousehold energy bills rise as
OL,4,Ctemperatures plummet
OL,6,FHowever experts at Cornwall Insight
OL,7,Fhave forecast energy bills to fall by
OL,8,F#138, or 8%, to #1,620 a year when the
OL,9,Fcap is next updated in April thanks to
OL,10,FGovernment measures announced in the
OL,11,Frecent budget.
OL,13,FChancellor Rachel Reeves said #150
OL,14,Fwould be cut from the average
OL,15,Fhousehold bill from April by scrapping
OL,16,Fthe Energy Company Obligation (Eco)
OL,17,Fscheme introduced by the Tories in
OL,18,Fgovernment.
