OL,6,F"The Chancellor's intervention in the
OL,7,FBudget to move a significant amount of
OL,8,Fpolicy costs into taxation was welcome
OL,9,Fand will provide much needed relief
OL,10,Ffor households across the country when
OL,11,Fthis comes into effect in April.
OL,13,F"However, even with this intervention,
OL,14,Fenergy bills are expected to remain
OL,15,Fwell above pre-energy crisis levels.
OL,16,FWith over six million households in
OL,17,Ffuel poverty and domestic energy debt
OL,18,Freaching record highs of around #5.5
OL,19,Fbillion, a comprehensive plan is
OL,20,Fneeded to further bring down bills and
OL,21,Ftruly address these challenges."
