OL,6,F"People continue to live in cold, damp
OL,7,Fhomes, where the risks go beyond
OL,8,Fdiscomfort and into real danger,
OL,9,Fincluding exposure to carbon monoxide.
OL,10,FYounger adults, private renters and
OL,11,Fhouseholds with children are among
OL,12,Fthose most at risk as people cut back
OL,13,Fon heating, delay repairs and try to
OL,14,Fblock draughts just to stay warm.
