OL,6,FWhich? energy editor Emily Seymour
OL,7,Fsaid: "As we head into the coldest
OL,8,Fmonths of the year, many households
OL,9,Fwill be concerned that the energy
OL,10,Fprice cap will increase slightly in
OL,11,Fthe new year.
OL,13,F"There are several deals on the market
OL,14,Ffor lower than the price cap so now is
OL,15,Fa good time to shop around if you're
OL,16,Flooking to fix. As a rule of thumb,
OL,17,Fwe'd recommend looking for deals
OL,18,Fcheaper than the current price cap,
OL,19,Fnot longer than 12 months and without
OL,20,Fsignificant exit fees.
