OL,3,CHousehold energy bills rise as
OL,4,Ctemperatures plummet
OL,6,F"But we need to be clear ` costs
OL,7,Faren't vanishing, they're shifting.
OL,8,FMoving the Renewables Obligation from
OL,9,Fbills to taxation may feel like a win,
OL,10,Fbut ultimately, it's still going to be
OL,11,Fpaid by the public.
OL,13,F"Crucially, as we move forward,
OL,14,Fvulnerable households must be
OL,15,Fprotected. Cutting bills today is
OL,16,Fwelcome, but without targeted support
OL,17,Fand a clear plan for fairer funding,
OL,18,Fthe benefits of net zero could bypass
OL,19,Fthose who need them most."
